1 WEEK TO GO TO MY @nasacademy LAUNCH!  Sign up here www.nasacademy.com/catriona 💥💥💥 Link in BIO 💃

✅ Open for ALL ages, genders and backgrounds 
✅ Not a "Pageant-Specific" course

In the Course, We'll Cover...
✅ Ways To Build Your Self-Confidence
✅ How To Deal With Anxiety & Self-Doubt
✅ How To Prepare For Major Presentations
✅ How To Handle Criticism & Rejection With Poise
...and much more! 

See you there! 👑

node.text:
Dedicated to all of our heroes of today that generations will look back upon and remember. 🙏 We may not have control of the circumstance, but we have control over ourselves and how we choose to see the world...how we choose to shape the world. Rise to the call of duty and selfless sacrifice, for within you is a hero, too. 

@binibiningnicolecordoves: "When the production team told us during our first script reading that we will be delivering a message of hope at the tail-end of the program, @catriona_gray immediately *raised her hand* and asked if we can write it ourselves.

We wrote this message together in the hopes that we get to tell the story of every Filipino in this pandemic
-a story of heartbreak and newfound hope.

And since we were already hosting the show, we decided the tone needs to be distinctly different. So we asked our Kuya Caloy to help us make it sound like spoken word poetry-stemming from his deep
love for our country, he added the fire and heart the message needed as well.

Sa panahon ng matinding pagsubok, ang "Lupang Hinirang" ang nagpapaalala sa atin ng taglay na
tapang ng mga Pilipino. Ito ang ating panata sa isa't-isa.

Huminga. Kumapit. Lumipad.

Artwork and animation by @vernversus"

I am #TeamEpson.

node.text:
Hey everyone, just checking in. I know I haven't been active much on social media lately. It's just that personally, it's become a bit much. Not social media alone, but just the news and the numbers. 

It feels like every week, there are condolences being shared on my timeline. Friends losing family. Friends losing friends. Families separated. People feeling isolated and alone fighting battles that seem too great.

But I just wanted to reach out, in this small way to let you who are reading this know, that whatever it is that you're facing or going through, you're not alone. Your feelings and your experiences are VALID. And no matter how big the challenges may seem, there is always hope to be found. God is greater than this and He is on your side.

Let me know in the comments how I can pray for you guys. 🙏 Sending you all a big, big hug.

Defy stress. Defy hairfall. Thanks to @creamsilkph Ultimate Hairfall Defiance with 3x Keratin for 3x stronger hair. 💚 #DefyToBeGreater

Thanks to my loves for helping me defy gravity 😜 📽@filmbyjololuarca 📸💄@jellyeugenio 💇‍♀️ @paulnebreshair 👗@justine.aliman19

node.text:
She's back. ⚡Glam, it's been a while. 

📸💄@jellyeugenio 💇‍♀️@paulnebreshair

You're not imagining it. Many of us feel like burning out, feel overwhelmed...feel tired. 
I've been struggling too, finding it hard to justify being away from my family during a time when I'm constantly searching for comfort amongst the uncertainty. 
Like many of you, I understand being called to the duty of providing for your loved ones (whether it be your families or your communities). But paying the price of being away from the people I love most has become more difficult to bear lately.
But faced with these challenges, I remember how far I've come and how much I've already overcome. And I choose to focus not on what is outside of my control, but on what IS. I choose to give myself grace for the moments I feel uncertain and unsure. I choose to rise above. 💫

Swipe to watch @creamsilkph 's new film on what it means to #DefyToBeGreater and defy hairfall with the New @creamsilk Hair Fall Defiance for ultimately stronger hair.

Let's choose to #DefyToBeGreater, together.
